{"type":"message","id":"a0c13416","parentId":"d2b35bae","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:49:38.424Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1vf18vroe7d1_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 223905\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to advance the Phase 1 goals, specifically the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The next action is to implement a TIC classifier on pulse log files.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action that advances this goal. I should implement the TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Classifies content as invariant vs variant across pulse logs\r\n2. Attempts to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThis would be a new Python script that processes the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs and validates against success criteria (>70% classification accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that analyzes pulse log files to identify invariant patterns and predict next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_INVARIANT_FREQ = 0.7  # Appears in 70%+ of pulses = invariant\r\n\r\ndef extract_concepts(pulse_text):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key concepts from pulse text.\"\"\"\r\n    # Extract headers, key terms, file references\r\n    concepts = set()\r\n    concepts.update(re.findall(r'`([^`]+)`', pulse_text))  # Code/file refs\r\n    concepts.update(re.findall(r'\\*\\*([^*]+)\\*\\*', pulse_text))  # Bold terms\r\n    concepts.update(re.findall(r'#+\\s+(\\w+)', pulse_text))  # Headers\r\n    return concepts\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as invariant (causal) vs variant.\"\"\"\r\n    all_concepts = Counter()\r\n    pulse_concepts = []\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        concepts = extract_concepts(pulse)\r\n        pulse_concepts.append(concepts)\r\n        all_concepts.update(concepts)\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears in >= MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ of pulses\r\n    invariants = {\r\n        c for c, freq in all_concepts.items() \r\n        if freq / len(pulses) >= MIN_INVARIANT_FREQ\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, pulse_concepts\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, last_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what next pulse will contain based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    last_concepts = extract_concepts(last_pulse)\r\n    predicted = invariants & last_concepts\r\n    return predicted\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    pulses = [f.read_text() for f in pulse_files]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulses) < 5:\r\n        print(\"Insufficient pulse data for TIC experiment\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Use first 80% for training, last 20% for testing\r\n    split = int(len(pulses) * 0.8)\r\n    train_pulses = pulses[:split]\r\n    test_pulses = pulses[split:]\r\n    \r\n    # Classify invariants from training set\r\n    invariants, train_concepts = classify_content(train_pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Test prediction: predict last pulse content from invariants\r\n    if test_pulses:\r\n        predicted = predict_next_pulse(invariants, test_pulses[-1])\r\n        actual = extract_concepts(test_pulses[-1])\r\n        prediction_acc = len(predicted & actual) / max(len(actual), 1) * 100\r\n    else:\r\n        prediction_acc = 0\r\n    \r\n    # Measure invariant ratio in test set\r\n    test_concepts = [extract_concepts(p) for p in test_pulses]\r\n    invariant_ratio = sum(len(c & invariants) for c in test_concepts)\r\n    total_concepts = sum(len(c) for c in test_concepts)\r\n    invariant_pct = invariant_ratio / max(total_concepts, 1) * 100\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"TIC Experiment Results\")\r\n    print(f\"=\" * 40)\r\n    print(f\"Training pulses: {split}\")\r\n    print(f\"Test pulses: {len(test_pulses)}\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariants found: {len(invariants)}\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariant ratio (test): {invariant_pct:.1f}%\")\r\n    print(f\"Next-pulse prediction: {prediction_acc:.1f}%\")\r\n    print(f\"\")\r\n    print(f\"Classification criterion: {'PASS' if invariant_pct >= 70 else 'FAIL'} (need 70%)\")\r\n    print(f\"Prediction criterion: {'PASS' if prediction_acc >= 60 else 'FAIL'} (need 60%)\")\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    main()\r\nfile: tic_classifier.py\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 22:39:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774320578417}}
